This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human-object interactions recognition and human pose estimation, which are both tasks related to computer vision. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques for end-to-end training further supports this categorization. The paper also involves the use of message passing and iterative learning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves the use of closed-loop systems, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of public benchmarks and datasets for evaluation suggests that this paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
